<br>
I like signature images; I like to see other peoples' creative efforts.  I also consider signature images a way to get an idea of the personality of the poster when I'm not in-game.  And I think there are things that can be better conveyed in the space of a reasonably-sized signature image than in the 60 x 60  icon space.<br>
<br>
I don't mind seeing signature images repeated in multiple posts in one thread (I mean, heck, you're only downloading the images once per page, right?), as long as they are reasonably sized and don't cause too much scrolling.<br>
<br>
Sound files or other plugins are probably a bad idea in signature files.  Scripts are probably a bad idea too.  <p><FONT FACE="verdana" SIZE=-2>
